      "title": "Video Frame Limit — usage",
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "Set your desired resolution, fps and duration. Connect the model for hidden_dim **auto-detection** (more accurate budget). The node displays detected VRAM, model class, and capped frame count on the canvas after each run.\n\nFormula: `max_frames = total_vram × safety_margin / (5 × (w÷8) × (h÷8) × hidden_dim × 2)`\n\nWire **width, height, frames, fps** to your video sampler. Use this node as the central config panel for the whole generation."
      ],
